data.name: EnhancedCustomShapeParameterType
desc: defines how an EnhancedCustomShapeParameter has to be interpreted

items.name: NORMAL
lines: the value of the point component is normal, the Coordinate is taken as it is

items.name: EQUATION
lines: the value of the point component has to be interpreted as index to an Equation

items.name: ADJUSTMENT
lines: the value of the point component has to be interpreted as index into the list of AdjustmentValues

items.name: LEFT
lines: the logical left border of the CustomShape is used

items.name: TOP
lines: the logical top border of the CustomShape is used

items.name: RIGHT
lines: the logical right border of the CustomShape is used

items.name: BOTTOM
lines: the logical bottom border of the CustomShape is used

items.name: XSTRETCH
lines: the x value of the stretch point is used

items.name: YSTRETCH
lines: the y value of the stretch point is used

items.name: HASSTROKE
lines: If the shape has a line style, a value of 1 is used.

items.name: HASFILL
lines: If the shape has a fill style, a value of 1 is used.

items.name: WIDTH
lines: The width of the svg:viewBox is used.

items.name: HEIGHT
lines: The height of the svg:viewBox is used.

items.name: LOGWIDTH
lines: The logical width of the shape is used.

items.name: LOGHEIGHT
lines: The logical height of the shape is used.
